## 6. System Health Logging — CPU/Memory Gap

The ObjC code logs CPU and memory on every tick via system APIs. In Swift/SDK context:

| Metric | ObjC source | Swift equivalent | Available in SDK? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Battery level | `UIDevice.batteryLevel` | `UIDevice.current.batteryLevel` | ✅ Yes |
| App run state | `[UIApplication sharedApplication]` | `AppRunState.$appRunState` | ✅ Yes |
| CPU usage | `task_info()` (private) | Not available without entitlement | ❌ No |
| Memory usage | `task_info()` / `mach_task_basic_info` | Not available without entitlement | ❌ No |
| Unity loaded | XPUnity SDK internal | N/A in vehicle SDK | ❌ N/A |

**Recommendation**: Log battery + app state only (as shown in `logSystemHealth()` above). If CPU/memory data is required, it must be passed in from the app layer via a `SystemInfoProvider` protocol:

```swift
protocol SystemInfoProvider {
    var cpuUsage: Double { get }       // 0.0–1.0
    var memoryUsageMB: Int { get }
}

// Inject into BLEKeepAliveMonitor, default to nil (logging skipped)
init(systemInfo: SystemInfoProvider? = nil, ...) { ... }
```

